{"type":"message","id":"519e2963","parentId":"c4381972","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:57:44.064Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rrvpok7hsycd_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 125714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment is complete with key findings\r\n3. Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment, distinguishing constant format tokens, implementing CFI filtering, wiring to TemporalAttention backend, designing compression network\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is:\r\n- Three-dimensional compression filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Need to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe next concrete action should be to run the hybrid scoring experiment. But first, I need to look at the current state of the research files to understand what's already been done.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what the current experiment status is. The pulse script runs MiniMax-M2.7 API call on each pulse. Let me think about what concrete file edit would advance the goals.\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next step based on the synthesis is:\r\n- Run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nBut I should look at the existing experiment files first to understand the current state. Let me check what's in the research directory.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md mentioned, this documents the experiment results. The next step is clearly the hybrid scoring experiment.\r\n\r\nBut as a stateless discontinuous agent, I should make a concrete file edit. The most logical action would be to either:\r\n1. Create a plan/experiment script for the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n2. Update the research with a new hypothesis based on the current findings\r\n3. Start implementing the three-dimensional filter\r\n\r\nGiven that the key finding is the three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120), the next experiment is to test Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring vs binary thresholds.\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment script or update the research plan. Let me create a concrete experiment plan for Strategy C.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on designing an experiment script that captures the nuanced scoring approach. The goal is to develop a hybrid method that balances token frequency and contextual feature importance, moving beyond binary thresholding. This requires careful parameter selection and a systematic testing methodology to validate the approach's effectiveness.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis established that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts while true research tokens have CFI<1. The next concrete step is implementing and testing the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate experiment script for Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring, implementing the formula and testing against the 200-pulse dataset to compare with binary threshold results.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (CFI=1.0, freq≈160 → score=1.0×1.0=1.0 - BUT we cap freq at 120)\r\n- Reward true research tokens (CFI=0.6, freq=40 → score=0.6×0.33=0.198)\r\n- Smooth out binary threshold cliff effects\r\n\r\n## Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Test Cases\r\n| Token | CFI | freq | Expected Score | Classification |\r\n|-------|-----|------|----------------|----------------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0×1.0 = 1.0 | FALSE POSITIVE (freq capped) |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 0.96×1.0 = 0.96 | TRUE (freq capped) |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 0.65 | 40 | 0.65×0.33 = 0.22 | TRUE |\r\n| \"context\" | 0.45 | 80 | 0.45×0.67 = 0.30 | TRUE |\r\n| \"xyz123\" | 0.05 | 1 | 0.05×0.008 = 0.0004 | FALSE |\r\n\r\n## Experiment\r\n1. Load 200-pulse dataset (pulse_*.md files)\r\n2. Calculate CFI and freq for all tokens\r\n3. Apply hybrid scoring formula\r\n4. Compare with ground truth (human-labeled research tokens)\r\n5. Report precision/recall vs Strategy A (freq-only) and Strategy B (CFI threshold)\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n- Reduce false positives from constant-format tokens\r\n- Maintain recall for research trajectory tokens\r\n- Smooth scoring surface for downstream compression network\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:57:38\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774371464062}}
